Wash and dry produce.

Dice @Roma Tomato{1}(diced). Halve, peel, and thinly slice @Yellow Onion{1}(halved, peeled, and thinly sliced); mince a few slices until you have 2 TBSP (4 TBSP for 4 servings). Zest and quarter @Lime{1}(zested and quartered). Mince @Jalapeño{1}(minced, ribs and seeds removed for less heat). Halve, core, and thinly slice @Long Green Pepper{1}(halved, cored, and thinly sliced into strips).

In a #small pot{}, combine @Jasmine Rice{1/2%cup}, 3/4 cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4 servings), and a big pinch of @Salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, in a #small bowl{}, combine tomato, minced onion, a squeeze of lime juice, and as much jalapeño as you like. Season with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}.

In a separate small bowl, combine @Sour Cream{4%tablespoon}, a squeeze of lime juice, and @Chili Powder{1/4%pinch} (you'll use the rest later). Season with salt and pepper. Stir in @water{1%tsp} 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{2%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add green pepper and sliced onion; cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and softened, ~{7-9%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper.

> Lower heat and add a splash of water if veggies begin to brown too quickly.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #medium bowl{} and cover to keep warm. Wipe out pan.

While veggies cook, pat @Chicken Breast Strips{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}.

Once veggies are done, heat another drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add chicken in a single layer, @Southwest Spice Blend{1%tablespoon}, and remaining chili powder. Cook, stirring occasionally, until chicken is browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Stir in @Chicken Stock Concentrate{1} and a splash of water; cook until saucy, ~{1-2%minutes}. Turn off heat. Season with salt and pepper.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @Butter{1%tablespoon} and lime zest. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide rice between #bowls{} and top with chicken and veggies. Drizzle with crema. Top with @Monterey Jack Cheese{1/4%cup} and pico de gallo. Serve with @Blue Corn Tortilla Chips{1.5%ounce} and remaining lime wedges on the side.

> For this fajita-inspired meal, feel free to go wild with assembly. Crema on bottom! Rice on top of chicken! Crush up your tortilla chips for a crunchy garnish, or serve along the side for scooping – that's the beauty of making it yourself!